# Day 0 – Create VPC with IPv6 Using Terraform

---

## Task Overview

As part of the AWS cloud migration strategy, the Nautilus DevOps team is provisioning network infrastructure using Terraform. To support modern networking standards and future scalability, the team needs to create a Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) with an Amazon-provided IPv6 CIDR block.

For this task, create a VPC named `datacenter-vpc` in the `us-east-1` region with an Amazon-generated IPv6 CIDR block using Terraform.

---

# Objective

| Property          | Value            |
| ----------------- | ---------------- |
| Resource Type     | VPC              |
| VPC Name          | `datacenter-vpc` |
| IPv6              | Amazon Provided  |
| Region            | `us-east-1`      |
| Provisioning Tool | Terraform        |

